\f0\b\fs42 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 2. Map Out Your Programmatic Song Structure\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 To keep your generated music from sounding like random, disjointed notes, your Python code needs a structural roadmap for each song loop. Sketch out a standard 3-minute arrangement template in your notes:\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f2\b\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Intro (16 bars):
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Code triggers just the ambient mall texture (mall_day_ambiance.mp3) and a basic, slow-fading electric piano chord progression.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f2\b\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 The Verse/Core (32 bars):
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Code activates your generated drum loop generation sequence (kick, snare, hi-hat) and kicks in the main melodic synth or guitar line.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f2\b\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 The Bridge/B-Section (16 bars):
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Code drops the drum layers completely. It modifies the filter cutoff to make the chords sound muffled, simulating a track playing from a speaker deep inside an empty store.\
